    s"Yes I am. She knows a hell of a lot about facial and body care, and she has extensive knowledge about skin biology and cosmetic chemistry."
    s"I think her services will be required when we start having plenty of guests checking into the hotel."
    s"And what I was also thinking is if we host any events that Ivy and Lily book for us here..."
    s"Then we can get Jazmin to do the girls makeup, any lash or brow treatments, manicures, pedicures, or any other required body treatments."
    mc"Damn, she seems more than qualified for that role."
    show sc day3hoteldinner d14
    s"And if you ever want a massage from her, she said she‚Äôd be more than happy to give you one."
    show sc day3hoteldinner d11
    s"Free of course to anyone who works at the hotel."
    mc"Haha, you won‚Äôt hear me saying no to a free massage!"
    show sc day3hoteldinner d14
    s"Haha, neither would I!"
    show sc day3hoteldinner d12
    s"So how did you find chatting and being alone with Ivy?"
    mc"Yeah, it was uh, interesting to say the least."
    show sc day3hoteldinner d11
    s"She has this very authoritative presence about her, doesn‚Äôt she?"
    mc"Oh yeah, it certainly came across like she‚Äôs a woman who knows what she wants, and what she wants is the very best."
    s"It still amazes me how different she and Lily are."
    s"Lily has a more bubbly personality and is incredibly easy to talk to, but I do love Ivy‚Äôs directness and the fact that she tells things like they are."
    s"She loves proving people wrong and it‚Äôs arguably her best quality."
    mc"I can relate to both girls from a work-ethic perspective."
    show sc day3hoteldinner d14
    s"Haha, so do you have a favourite of the twins then?"
    show sc day3hoteldinner d07
    s"I promise you I won‚Äôt tell either of them what your answer is."
    show sc day3hoteldinner d11
    mc"Well, just between you and me‚Ä¶"
    # [Ivy / Lily / Both equally]"
    menu:
        "Ivy":
            show sc day3hoteldinner d12
            mc"I like how well they work together and they obviously have very high standards, something that I can appreciate."
            mc"But I‚Äôd say I like Ivy more because she likes to be the one in control, something that I‚Äôve always wanted to be in all my years in law."
            mc"I always strived to be the top dog, but as you know, I didn‚Äôt quite get there."
            show sc day3hoteldinner d11
            s"Maybe you didn‚Äôt, but being the top dog in the hotel industry here in Sunshine Bay one day would be just as satisfying, don‚Äôt you think?"
            $ tw_points = change_stat(tw_points,1,"Lily and Ivy")
            mc"Haha, it sure would. Maybe there are some tips in leadership that I could learn from Ivy." # +1 Twins Point"
        "Lily":
            show sc day3hoteldinner d12
            mc"I like how well they work together and they obviously have very high standards, something that I can appreciate."
            mc"But I‚Äôd say I like Lily more because as you said, it feels like she‚Äôs the more approachable of the two and seems like she‚Äôd be a lot of fun."
            mc"That‚Äôs not to say Ivy wouldn‚Äôt be as well, but when I‚Äôve spoken to Lily, she has given off a more chilled, easy-going vibe."
            mc"I really like that in a person."
            show sc day3hoteldinner d11
            s"That‚Äôs understandable. Lily epitomises the relaxed feeling of most of the people in this town."
            $ tw_points = change_stat(tw_points,1,"Lily and Ivy")
            s"I can see why you would like her more." #+1 Twins Point"

        "Both equally"(wt="Best choice"):
            show sc day3hoteldinner d12
            mc"I like how well they work together and they obviously have very high standards, something that I can appreciate."
            mc"I admire Ivy because she likes to be the one in control, something that I‚Äôve always wanted to be in all my years in law."
            mc"I always strived to be the top dog, but as you know, I didn‚Äôt quite get there."
            mc"However, there are qualities that I like about Lily too, because as you said, it feels like she‚Äôs the more approachable of the two and seems like she‚Äôd be a lot of fun."
            mc"That‚Äôs not to say Ivy wouldn‚Äôt be as well, but when I‚Äôve spoken to Lily, she has given off a more chilled, easy-going vibe."
            mc"I really like that in a person."
            mc"So to answer your question, I like them both equally."
            show sc day3hoteldinner d14
            s"Haha, good answer [y_name]."
            show sc day3hoteldinner d11
            $ tw_points = change_stat(tw_points,2,"Lily and Ivy")
            s"I‚Äôd say I like them equally too. It‚Äôs very hard to split them!" #+2 Twins Point"
            # (scene continues)"
    show sc day3hoteldinner d12
    s"So you were saying earlier on that you didn't have too much trouble getting the tools from Randy, right?"
    mc"Uh yeah, kind of."
    mc"He didn‚Äôt have them at his home because he was doing some odd job at the church just before his injury, and he ended up leaving them there."
    show sc day3hoteldinner d08
    s"Oh, typical Randy."
    show sc day3hoteldinner d12
    s"Let me guess, he was persuaded by some cute blonde girl there at the church, right?"
    mc"Well, he did mention that he'd been in contact with a girl at the church who would meet me when I arrived there."
    mc"Randy called her beforehand, just before I left his place. Her name is [k_name]."
    s"Yeah, I know who she is. She‚Äôs Ivy and Lily‚Äôs younger sister."
    mc"So I was told. Do you not like her?"
    s"Oh no, don‚Äôt get me wrong, I don‚Äôt have any issues with [k_name]."
    show sc day3hoteldinner d13
    s"I‚Äôm just pissed off with Randy for leaving the tools at the church and sending you over there to go and get them."
    show sc day3hoteldinner d14
    s"He has a bit of crush on [k_name] you see, even though she is sooo not his type."
    show sc day3hoteldinner d11
    mc"(I better not tell [s_name] exactly how much trouble I had to go through to get these tools for her.)"
    show sc day3hoteldinner d12
    mc"Really? Well getting the tools wasn‚Äôt too much of a problem. [k_name] was pretty helpful."
    show sc day3hoteldinner d11
    s"Is that right? You mean she didn‚Äôt try and convert you into becoming a part of their community, did she?"
    mc"No, she didn‚Äôt, which was pretty surprising."
    show sc day3hoteldinner d06
    s"It‚Äôs hard to understand why she would want to spend most of her time there at the church when she could be experiencing what the rest of the world has to offer."
    s"I think her father must have her completely brainwashed."
    show sc day3hoteldinner d12
    mc"(Ivy told me that [k_name] isn‚Äôt quite the goody-goody Daddy‚Äôs girl that everyone thinks she is.)"
    mc"(I don‚Äôt think she's told [s_name] this however. Maybe I should keep that to myself until I find out for sure.)"
    mc"Well, the main thing is I got the tools back."
    mc"And there‚Äôs something else I wanted to discuss with you [s_name] that I spoke to Ivy about regarding [k_name]."
    mc"Ivy suggested that we get someone to re-design the events hall, and despite their differences, she also said that it would be a good idea for us to hire her little sister."
    mc"[k_name] told me that she‚Äôs currently studying interior design at college, and perhaps we could hire her at a cheaper rate to fix up the hall."
    mc"It all depends if she‚Äôs interested in working with us of course."
    mc"What do you think?"
    show sc day3hoteldinner d14
    s"That sounds great!"
    show sc day3hoteldinner d11
    s"If you can organise this with [k_name] and work out the costs, how much time it would take to do the work, then by all means [y_name]."
    mc"Great! I‚Äôll see if I can meet with her tomorrow."
    show sc day3hoteldinner d07
    s"Mmm‚Ä¶ I‚Äôm just about done here with dinner. You?"
    mc"Yeah, I‚Äôm pretty full. Thanks again for this [s_name], it was magnificent."
    show sc day3hoteldinner d14
    s"You‚Äôre welcome. I‚Äôm just happy I could finally sit down to have a home-cooked dinner with you."
    show sc day3hoteldinner d11
    s"But the night isn‚Äôt over yet!"
    s"Why don‚Äôt you take this bottle of wine and our glasses into the next room while I clean up here and set the dishwasher?"
    show sc day3hoteldinner d12
    mc"Oh, you don‚Äôt want a hand with it?"
    # (Friend and the MC stand)"
    show sc day3hoteldinner d11
    s"No, it‚Äôs your night to relax, let me take care of this for you. I‚Äôll come and join you shortly."
    s"Maybe we can watch some TV or talk more about the hotel if you‚Äôd like?"
    mc"That would be nice."
    show sc day3hoteldinner d16
    mc"I'm going to take a shower and get changed first if you don't mind?"
    show sc day3hoteldinner d17
    s"Haha no worries. I might do that too."
